1
00:01:25,469 --> 00:01:27,637
Where's my suitcase?

2
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:31,808
Who stole the hair dryer?

3
00:01:31,976 --> 00:01:33,434
Miss. Young lady!

4
00:01:33,644 --> 00:01:35,520
Excuse me. Girls!

5
00:01:36,188 --> 00:01:38,523
Hey, little fella. Hey!

6
00:01:38,732 --> 00:01:41,067
Excuse me, girls. Girls!

7
00:01:41,902 --> 00:01:42,902
Hey, big fella!

8
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:45,280
Help me make the beds
in the living room.

9
00:01:45,489 --> 00:01:46,656
Come on down here!

10
00:01:46,907 --> 00:01:48,825
Hey, son!

11
00:01:49,743 --> 00:01:53,079
Big fella.
Hey, little guy! Little guy!

12
00:01:54,498 --> 00:01:57,250
Pete's brother
and his family are here.

13
00:01:57,459 --> 00:01:59,002
Trish is going to Montreal.

14
00:01:59,211 --> 00:02:01,754
Montreal? Oh, her family's there.

15
00:02:02,006 --> 00:02:03,423
-Then we're off.
-When?

16
00:02:03,632 --> 00:02:05,925
-Tomorrow.
-You're not ready, are you?

17
00:02:06,552 --> 00:02:09,053
Uncle Frank won't let me
watch the movie...

18
00:02:09,263 --> 00:02:10,597
...but the big kids can.

19
00:02:10,848 --> 00:02:12,098
Why can't I?

20
00:02:12,308 --> 00:02:13,474
I'm on the phone.

21
00:02:14,435 --> 00:02:16,561
When do you come back?
Not till then?

22
00:02:16,770 --> 00:02:19,606
It's not even rated R.
He's just being a jerk.

23
00:02:20,733 --> 00:02:23,318
Kevin, if Uncle Frank says no...

24
00:02:23,527 --> 00:02:25,153
...then it must be really bad.

25
00:02:25,446 --> 00:02:28,531
No, we put the dog in the kennel--
Hey, get off!

26
00:02:28,741 --> 00:02:29,949
Kevin, out of the room.

27
00:02:30,117 --> 00:02:32,452
Hang up the phone and make me,
why don't you?

28
00:02:32,620 --> 00:02:33,661
This kid.

29
00:02:33,829 --> 00:02:36,372
Did you pick up
a voltage adapter thing?

30
00:02:36,582 --> 00:02:38,124
No, I didn't have time.

31
00:02:38,334 --> 00:02:41,085
-Then how do I shave in France?
-Grow a goatee.

32
00:02:41,295 --> 00:02:43,463
Dad, nobody'll let me do anything.

33
00:02:43,631 --> 00:02:47,967
I've got something, pick up those
Micro Machines that are all over.

34
00:02:48,135 --> 00:02:50,136
Aunt Leslie almost broke her neck.

35
00:02:50,346 --> 00:02:52,680
He was playing
with the glue gun again.

36
00:02:53,098 --> 00:02:54,182
We talked about that.

37
00:02:54,558 --> 00:02:57,477
Did I burn down the joint?
I don't think so.

38
00:02:57,645 --> 00:02:59,520
I made ornaments out of fish hooks.

39
00:03:00,397 --> 00:03:03,691
-My new fish hooks?
-I can't make them out of old ones...

40
00:03:03,984 --> 00:03:06,277
...with dry worm guts stuck on them.

41
00:03:07,279 --> 00:03:10,240
-Peter.
-Come on, Kevin. Out.

42
00:03:10,616 --> 00:03:12,700
Do you guys have a voltage adapter?

43
00:03:12,910 --> 00:03:14,369
Here's a voltage adapter!

44
00:03:14,578 --> 00:03:18,206
God, you're getting heavy!
Go pack your suitcase.

45
00:03:19,583 --> 00:03:22,502
Pack my suitcase?

46
00:03:23,003 --> 00:03:25,129
-Where's the shampoo?
-I don't live here.

47
00:03:25,339 --> 00:03:27,507
This many people here
and no shampoo.

48
00:03:27,675 --> 00:03:29,842
-Are your folks home?
-They don't live here.

49
00:03:30,010 --> 00:03:32,679
-Tracy, did you order the pizza?
-Buzz did.

50
00:03:32,888 --> 00:03:34,889
Excuse me. Are your parents here?

51
00:03:35,140 --> 00:03:36,599
My parents live in Paris.

52
00:03:36,767 --> 00:03:37,850
-Hi!
-Hi!

53
00:03:38,018 --> 00:03:39,394
-Are your parents home?
-Yeah.

54
00:03:39,561 --> 00:03:41,479
-Do they live here?
-No.

55
00:03:41,647 --> 00:03:45,358
No. Why should they?
All kids, no parents.

56
00:03:45,609 --> 00:03:46,943
Probably a fancy orphanage.

57
00:03:47,403 --> 00:03:51,114
I don't know how to pack a suitcase.
I've never done it once.

58
00:03:51,323 --> 00:03:53,449
-Tough.
-That's what Megan said.

59
00:03:53,659 --> 00:03:56,160
-What did I say?
-You told him, "Tough."

60
00:03:56,370 --> 00:03:59,706
The dope was whining about a suitcase.
What was I supposed to say?

61
00:03:59,873 --> 00:04:01,582
"Congratulations, you're an idiot"?

62
00:04:01,792 --> 00:04:03,334
-I'm not an idiot!
-Really?

63
00:04:03,544 --> 00:04:06,629
You're helpless! We have to do
everything for you.

64
00:04:06,839 --> 00:04:10,049
-She's right, Kev.
-Excuse me, puke-breath. I'm small.

65
00:04:10,259 --> 00:04:11,884
I don't know how to pack.

66
00:04:12,094 --> 00:04:15,430
-I hope you didn't just pack crap.
-Shut up, Linnie.

67
00:04:15,597 --> 00:04:18,599
-Do you know what I should pack?
-Buzz told you, cheek-face.

68
00:04:18,767 --> 00:04:20,560
Toilet paper and water.

69
00:04:21,937 --> 00:04:23,688
What are you so worried about?

70
00:04:23,897 --> 00:04:26,482
You know Mom's gonna
pack your stuff, anyway.

71
00:04:26,734 --> 00:04:29,819
You're what the French call
les incompetents.

72
00:04:30,070 --> 00:04:31,070
What?

73
00:04:32,323 --> 00:04:33,906
Bombs away!

74
00:04:38,162 --> 00:04:41,873
P.S. You have to sleep
on the hide-a-bed with Fuller.

75
00:04:42,082 --> 00:04:45,209
If he has something to drink,
he'll wet the bed.

76
00:04:46,003 --> 00:04:48,755
This house is so full of people
it makes me sick!

77
00:04:48,964 --> 00:04:51,716
When I grow up and get married,
I'm living alone!

78
00:04:51,925 --> 00:04:54,719
Did you hear me?
I'm living alone!

79
00:04:55,471 --> 00:04:57,597
I'm living alone!

80
00:05:00,351 --> 00:05:02,352
Who's gonna feed your spider?

81
00:05:03,103 --> 00:05:06,856
He just ate a load of mice guts.
He'll be good for a couple weeks.

82
00:05:08,609 --> 00:05:11,486
Is it true French babes
don't shave their pits?

83
00:05:12,154 --> 00:05:13,196
Some don't.

84
00:05:14,740 --> 00:05:16,240
But they got nude beaches.

85
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:17,658
Not in the winter.

86
00:05:23,999 --> 00:05:25,541
Buzz?

87
00:05:25,709 --> 00:05:27,835
Don't you know how to knock,
phlegm-wad?

88
00:05:28,253 --> 00:05:31,464
Can I sleep here?
I don't want to sleep with Fuller.

89
00:05:31,673 --> 00:05:33,508
If he drinks, he'll wet the bed.

90
00:05:34,134 --> 00:05:38,304
I wouldn't let you sleep in my room
if you were growing on my ass.

91
00:05:41,642 --> 00:05:43,726
Check it out. Old man Marley.

92
00:05:47,731 --> 00:05:48,773
Who's he?

93
00:05:49,566 --> 00:05:53,027
You ever heard of
the South Bend Shovel Slayer?

94
00:05:53,195 --> 00:05:55,071
-No.
-That's him.

95
00:05:55,280 --> 00:06:00,159
In '58 he murdered his whole family
and half the people on his block...

96
00:06:01,286 --> 00:06:03,287
...with a snow shovel.

97
00:06:03,789 --> 00:06:06,791
Been hiding out
in this neighborhood ever since.

98
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:10,545
If he's the shovel slayer,
how come the cops don't arrest him?

99
00:06:10,754 --> 00:06:12,505
Not enough evidence to convict.

100
00:06:13,215 --> 00:06:15,258
They never found the bodies.

101
00:06:15,509 --> 00:06:17,552
Everyone around here knows he did it.

102
00:06:18,178 --> 00:06:20,012
It'll just be a matter of time...

103
00:06:20,222 --> 00:06:22,265
...before he does it again.

104
00:06:22,474 --> 00:06:24,142
What's he doing now?

105
00:06:24,309 --> 00:06:27,270
He walks up and down
the streets every night...

106
00:06:27,479 --> 00:06:29,772
...salting the sidewalks.

107
00:06:29,982 --> 00:06:31,941
Maybe he's just trying to be nice.

108
00:06:33,694 --> 00:06:35,361
No way.

109
00:06:35,988 --> 00:06:38,448
See that garbage can full of salt?

110
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:41,909
That's where he keeps his victims.

111
00:06:42,119 --> 00:06:44,912
The salt turns the bodies...

112
00:06:45,205 --> 00:06:46,956
...into mummies.

113
00:06:49,418 --> 00:06:50,960
Mummies!

114
00:06:55,507 --> 00:06:56,757
Look out!

115
00:07:29,625 --> 00:07:32,043
How you kids doing? Good?

116
00:07:32,669 --> 00:07:34,837
Lot of action around here today, huh?

117
00:07:35,047 --> 00:07:36,631
Going on vacation?

118
00:07:36,924 --> 00:07:38,382
Where you going?

119
00:07:38,592 --> 00:07:42,053
You hear me, or what?
Going on a trip?

120
00:07:42,554 --> 00:07:44,263
Where you going, kid?

121
00:07:53,607 --> 00:07:56,526
Okay, that's $122.50.

122
00:07:56,944 --> 00:07:59,028
Not from me, kid. I don't live here.

123
00:07:59,279 --> 00:08:01,280
You just around for the holidays?

124
00:08:01,448 --> 00:08:02,782
You could say that.

125
00:08:02,950 --> 00:08:04,534
-Pizza's here!
-There you go.

126
00:08:04,785 --> 00:08:06,702
That's $122.50.

127
00:08:06,954 --> 00:08:08,955
It's my brother's house. He'll get it.

128
00:08:10,582 --> 00:08:12,291
Hey, listen....

129
00:08:13,001 --> 00:08:14,085
-Hi.
-Hi.

130
00:08:14,628 --> 00:08:16,504
-Are you Mr. McCallister?
-Yeah.

131
00:08:16,713 --> 00:08:18,548
The Mr. McCallister who lives here?

132
00:08:18,799 --> 00:08:21,217
Good, because somebody
owes me $122.50.

133
00:08:21,385 --> 00:08:24,971
-I'd like a word with you, sir.
-Am I under arrest or something?

134
00:08:25,138 --> 00:08:29,058
No, no, no. There's always
a lot of burglaries around the holidays.

135
00:08:29,309 --> 00:08:33,354
We're checking the neighborhood to see
if the proper precautions are taken.

136
00:08:34,606 --> 00:08:37,608
We have automatic timers
for our lights, locks for our doors.

137
00:08:37,818 --> 00:08:39,819
That's about as well
as anybody can do.

138
00:08:40,028 --> 00:08:42,071
-Did you get some eggnog?
-Come on.

139
00:08:42,322 --> 00:08:43,698
-Let's eat.
-Come on.

140
00:08:43,865 --> 00:08:44,907
-Eggnog?
-Pizza!

141
00:08:45,117 --> 00:08:48,452
-Are you gonna be leaving--?
-Pizza!

142
00:08:49,496 --> 00:08:51,414
Grab a napkin
and pour your own drinks.

143
00:08:51,623 --> 00:08:56,335
-Does Santa go through customs?
-What time do we have to go to bed?

144
00:08:56,503 --> 00:08:59,380
Early. We're leaving at 8 a.m.
on the button.

145
00:08:59,590 --> 00:09:03,342
I hope you're all drinking milk.
I want to get rid of it.

146
00:09:03,552 --> 00:09:08,139
-Pizza boy needs $122.50, plus tip.
-For pizza?

147
00:09:08,348 --> 00:09:10,099
Ten pizzas times 12 bucks.

148
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:12,727
-You've got money.
-Traveler's checks.

149
00:09:12,936 --> 00:09:15,021
Forget it, Frank. We have cash.

150
00:09:15,230 --> 00:09:18,399
You probably got the checks
that don't work in France.

151
00:09:18,859 --> 00:09:21,527
Did anyone order me a plain cheese?

152
00:09:21,862 --> 00:09:23,863
Yeah. But if you want any...

153
00:09:24,114 --> 00:09:27,366
...somebody's gonna have to barf it up
because it's gone.

154
00:09:27,909 --> 00:09:31,454
Fuller! Go easy on the Pepsi.

155
00:09:37,586 --> 00:09:40,254
Kev! Kev, get a plate.

156
00:09:50,724 --> 00:09:53,059
-Passports!
-Watch it!

157
00:09:56,438 --> 00:09:58,981
No, no. Get these passports
out of here.

158
00:10:03,445 --> 00:10:06,405
Are you okay, honey? Come here.
Are you all right?

159
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,324
What is the matter?

160
00:10:08,659 --> 00:10:11,285
He started it!
He ate my pizza on purpose.

161
00:10:11,620 --> 00:10:13,537
He knows I hate sausage and olives--

162
00:10:13,747 --> 00:10:16,207
Look what you did, you little jerk!

163
00:10:29,930 --> 00:10:31,138
Get upstairs now.

164
00:10:31,306 --> 00:10:32,348
Why?

165
00:10:32,557 --> 00:10:34,225
You're such a disease.

166
00:10:34,476 --> 00:10:36,811
-Shut up!
-Kevin, upstairs!

167
00:10:37,020 --> 00:10:39,188
-Say good night, Kevin.
-"Good night, Kevin."

168
00:10:42,150 --> 00:10:44,026
Why do I get treated like scum?

169
00:10:44,236 --> 00:10:46,821
I'm sorry. This house is just crazy.

170
00:10:47,072 --> 00:10:49,281
We've got all these extra kids
running around.

171
00:10:49,491 --> 00:10:52,535
My brother's in from Ohio.
It's nuts.

172
00:10:52,786 --> 00:10:55,287
How come you didn't bring
more cheese pizzas?

173
00:10:56,248 --> 00:10:58,541
-Nice tip. Thanks.
-Thanks.

174
00:10:58,709 --> 00:10:59,959
Having a reunion?

175
00:11:00,127 --> 00:11:04,463
My husband's brother transferred
to Paris. His kids are still here.

176
00:11:04,715 --> 00:11:07,341
He missed the family,
so he invited us to Paris...

177
00:11:07,551 --> 00:11:08,718
...so we'll be together.

178
00:11:08,969 --> 00:11:12,513
-You're taking a trip to Paris?
-Yes, we leave tomorrow morning.

179
00:11:13,557 --> 00:11:14,890
Excellent. Excellent.

180
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:18,144
If you'll excuse me,
this one's a little out of sorts.

181
00:11:18,353 --> 00:11:21,063
Don't worry about me.
I spoke to your husband.

182
00:11:21,481 --> 00:11:26,110
And don't worry about your home.
It's in good hands.

183
00:11:29,197 --> 00:11:32,158
Fifteen people in this house,
and only you have to make trouble.

184
00:11:32,367 --> 00:11:33,743
I'm getting dumped on.

185
00:11:33,994 --> 00:11:36,746
You're the only one acting up.
Now get upstairs.

186
00:11:36,997 --> 00:11:39,290
I am upstairs, dummy!

187
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,667
The third floor?

188
00:11:41,877 --> 00:11:44,044
-Go.
-It's scary up there.

189
00:11:44,254 --> 00:11:46,130
Fuller'll be up in a while.

190
00:11:46,339 --> 00:11:49,383
I don't want to sleep with Fuller.
He wets the bed.

191
00:11:49,593 --> 00:11:51,802
He'll pee all over me. I know it.

192
00:11:52,053 --> 00:11:53,804
We'll put him somewhere else.

193
00:11:55,098 --> 00:11:56,432
I'm sorry.

194
00:11:56,767 --> 00:11:59,059
It's too late. Get upstairs.

195
00:12:02,230 --> 00:12:04,148
Everyone in this family hates me!

196
00:12:04,357 --> 00:12:06,525
Then ask Santa for a new family.

197
00:12:06,735 --> 00:12:10,196
I don't want a new family.
I don't want any family. Families suck!

198
00:12:10,405 --> 00:12:13,532
Stay up there. I don't want
to see you again tonight.

199
00:12:13,742 --> 00:12:16,243
I don't want to see you
for the rest of my life.

200
00:12:16,453 --> 00:12:18,913
I don't want to see
anybody else either.

201
00:12:19,164 --> 00:12:21,123
I hope you don't mean that.

202
00:12:21,374 --> 00:12:25,211
You'd feel pretty sad if you woke up
and didn't have a family.

203
00:12:25,962 --> 00:12:27,421
No, I wouldn't.

204
00:12:27,631 --> 00:12:30,216
Then say it again. Maybe it'll happen.

205
00:12:30,425 --> 00:12:33,636
I hope I never see
any of you jerks again!

206
00:12:54,366 --> 00:12:57,493
I wish they would all just disappear.

207
00:13:54,384 --> 00:13:57,720
-Where are they?
-I don't know. She said 8 sharp.

208
00:14:06,187 --> 00:14:07,646
Peter!

209
00:14:09,733 --> 00:14:11,525
-We slept in!
-We slept in!

210
00:14:28,376 --> 00:14:31,253
Hi, I'm Mitch Murphy.
I live across the street.

211
00:14:31,463 --> 00:14:33,255
You guys going out of town?

212
00:14:33,506 --> 00:14:34,840
We're going to Florida.

213
00:14:35,050 --> 00:14:38,677
Well, first we're going to Missouri
to pick up my grandma.

214
00:14:38,887 --> 00:14:41,388
You know the McCallisters
are going to France?

215
00:14:41,598 --> 00:14:42,973
Do you know if it's cold?

216
00:14:43,183 --> 00:14:47,770
-Do these vans get good mileage?
-Kid, I don't know. Hit the road!

217
00:14:51,441 --> 00:14:53,692
Do a head count.
Get everyone in the vans.

218
00:14:53,902 --> 00:14:55,110
Where are the passports?

219
00:14:55,362 --> 00:14:57,237
I put them in the microwave to dry.

220
00:14:57,489 --> 00:15:01,241
How fast does this go?
Does it have automatic transmission?

221
00:15:01,451 --> 00:15:03,243
Does it have 4-wheel drive?

222
00:15:03,453 --> 00:15:07,331
Look, I told you before, kid.
Don't bother me. Now, beat it!

223
00:15:18,843 --> 00:15:21,011
Line up in front of the van.

224
00:15:22,847 --> 00:15:24,932
Line up and shut up!

225
00:15:25,141 --> 00:15:27,851
Shut up! I gotta take a head count.

226
00:15:28,395 --> 00:15:29,436
One, two, three--

227
00:15:29,646 --> 00:15:32,022
Eleven, 92, 12....

228
00:15:32,732 --> 00:15:34,608
Buzz, don't be a moron.

229
00:15:34,859 --> 00:15:37,736
Six, seven, eight...

230
00:15:37,946 --> 00:15:40,531
...nine, 10, 11.

231
00:15:40,824 --> 00:15:44,576
Okay, half in this van,
half in this one. Let's go.

232
00:15:45,745 --> 00:15:48,539
Have a good trip.
Bring me back something French.

233
00:15:51,292 --> 00:15:55,087
There's no way we'll make this plane.
It leaves in 45 minutes.

234
00:15:55,296 --> 00:15:56,547
Think positive!

235
00:15:56,756 --> 00:15:58,674
You be positive. I'll be realistic.

236
00:15:58,842 --> 00:16:02,428
Ma'am. Ma'am.
Excuse me, your power is fixed...

237
00:16:02,637 --> 00:16:06,265
...but the phones are a mess.
It'll take a couple of days to fix.

238
00:16:06,433 --> 00:16:08,851
-Especially around the holidays.
-Thanks.

239
00:16:09,060 --> 00:16:10,394
Did you count heads?

240
00:16:11,187 --> 00:16:12,396
Eleven, including me.

241
00:16:12,605 --> 00:16:17,192
Five boys, six girls, four parents, two
drivers, and a partridge in a pear tree.

242
00:16:53,021 --> 00:16:54,354
Hold the plane!

243
00:16:54,814 --> 00:16:56,482
-Did we miss it?
-You just made it.

244
00:16:58,359 --> 00:17:01,361
Single seats only in coach.
Take whatever's free.

245
00:17:02,655 --> 00:17:04,323
I get a window seat!

246
00:17:07,327 --> 00:17:10,954
-Kids are in coach, we're first class.
-Seats Four A and B.

247
00:17:11,164 --> 00:17:13,624
Four A and B. I'll take your coats.

248
00:17:15,043 --> 00:17:17,252
-Fasten your seat belts.
-Champagne, please.

249
00:17:17,462 --> 00:17:19,588
-It's free, isn't it?
-Oh, yes.

250
00:17:20,507 --> 00:17:21,632
We made it.

251
00:17:21,841 --> 00:17:25,594
Do you believe it?
Hope we didn't forget anything.

252
00:18:46,509 --> 00:18:47,593
Mom?

253
00:18:53,141 --> 00:18:54,933
Thank you.

254
00:18:55,143 --> 00:18:58,478
-That's real. That's real crystal.
-Yeah, so?

255
00:18:58,688 --> 00:19:01,607
-Put them in your purse.
-Frank, I can't do that.

256
00:19:01,816 --> 00:19:04,568
Just-- Put them in your purse!

257
00:19:04,944 --> 00:19:07,446
Yeah. Fill it up. Fill it up.

258
00:19:07,655 --> 00:19:08,989
Fill it up, please.

259
00:19:09,949 --> 00:19:10,949
Thank you.

260
00:19:11,117 --> 00:19:14,703
Don't you feel like a heel,
flying first class with the kids in coach?

261
00:19:14,954 --> 00:19:16,288
No. The kids are fine.

262
00:19:16,497 --> 00:19:20,792
The only time I ever flew as a kid was
in the station wagon, not to France.

263
00:19:21,085 --> 00:19:23,962
We had to go to Aunt Laura
and Uncle Arthur's.

264
00:19:24,464 --> 00:19:27,341
Kids are okay. They're having
the time of their lives.

265
00:19:28,468 --> 00:19:30,052
Hello?

266
00:19:31,638 --> 00:19:32,971
Mom?

267
00:19:35,350 --> 00:19:36,808
Dad?

268
00:19:40,521 --> 00:19:43,649
Mom? Dad?

269
00:19:45,526 --> 00:19:47,569
Where are you guys?

270
00:19:48,488 --> 00:19:49,863
Buzz?

271
00:19:51,491 --> 00:19:53,283
Buzz?

272
00:19:56,537 --> 00:19:58,664
Buzz?

273
00:20:03,044 --> 00:20:04,294
Megan?

274
00:20:04,796 --> 00:20:06,171
Hello?

275
00:20:07,006 --> 00:20:08,882
Hello?

276
00:20:09,050 --> 00:20:10,342
Rod?

277
00:20:10,551 --> 00:20:12,010
Uncle Frank?

278
00:20:12,178 --> 00:20:14,888
Uncle Frank, is this a joke?

279
00:20:16,391 --> 00:20:19,601
Megan? Linnie?

280
00:20:21,896 --> 00:20:23,939
Is this a joke?

281
00:20:47,588 --> 00:20:49,339
It's only my imagination.

282
00:20:49,549 --> 00:20:51,550
Only my imagination.

283
00:21:08,985 --> 00:21:12,112
The cars are still here.
They didn't go to the airport!

284
00:21:30,131 --> 00:21:33,633
I made my family disappear.

285
00:21:34,927 --> 00:21:36,845
You're completely helpless.

286
00:21:37,096 --> 00:21:41,892
You know, Kevin, you're what
the French call les incompetents.

287
00:21:42,143 --> 00:21:45,103
Kevin, I'm going to feed you
to my tarantula.

288
00:21:45,271 --> 00:21:48,106
Kevin, you are such a disease.

289
00:21:48,316 --> 00:21:53,278
There are 15 people, and you're
the only one who has to make trouble.

290
00:21:53,613 --> 00:21:57,115
Look what you did, you little jerk!

291
00:22:00,661 --> 00:22:04,247
I made my family disappear.

292
00:22:18,304 --> 00:22:20,138
I'm free!

293
00:22:40,243 --> 00:22:43,453
No clothes on anybody. Sickening!

294
00:22:44,497 --> 00:22:47,999
Cool! Firecrackers!
I'll save these for later.

295
00:22:48,459 --> 00:22:51,169
Buzz, I'm going through
all your private stuff.

296
00:22:51,421 --> 00:22:53,964
You better come out and pound me!

297
00:22:57,969 --> 00:23:01,012
Buzz, your girlfriend! Woof!

298
00:23:50,021 --> 00:23:51,396
Who is it?

299
00:23:55,067 --> 00:23:57,944
It's me, Snakes. I got the stuff.

300
00:23:58,237 --> 00:24:00,989
Leave it on the doorstep
and get the hell out.

301
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:04,326
All right, Johnny,
but what about my money?

302
00:24:04,535 --> 00:24:05,577
What money?

303
00:24:05,786 --> 00:24:08,038
A.C. said you had some dough for me.

304
00:24:08,247 --> 00:24:11,166
Is that a fact?
How much do I owe you?

305
00:24:11,375 --> 00:24:13,293
A.C. said 10 percent.

306
00:24:14,462 --> 00:24:16,922
Too bad A.C. ain't in charge no more.

307
00:24:17,798 --> 00:24:20,091
Guys, I'm eating junk
and watching rubbish!

308
00:24:20,301 --> 00:24:22,844
You better come out and stop me!

309
00:24:23,054 --> 00:24:25,180
He'll call you when he gets out.

310
00:24:26,724 --> 00:24:28,099
Hey.

311
00:24:28,351 --> 00:24:30,352
I'll tell you what I'll give you.

312
00:24:31,979 --> 00:24:34,272
I'm gonna give you
to the count of 10...

313
00:24:34,982 --> 00:24:37,275
...to get your ugly, yellow...

314
00:24:37,485 --> 00:24:39,653
...no-good keister off my property...

315
00:24:39,862 --> 00:24:41,863
...before I pump your guts
full of lead.

316
00:24:42,073 --> 00:24:44,699
All right, I'm sorry. I'm going.

317
00:24:44,951 --> 00:24:47,160
One, two...10.

318
00:25:02,593 --> 00:25:04,803
Keep the change, you filthy animal.

319
00:25:06,722 --> 00:25:08,056
Mom!

320
00:25:19,360 --> 00:25:20,694
What's the matter?

321
00:25:22,154 --> 00:25:23,321
Honey?

322
00:25:24,699 --> 00:25:28,118
-I have a terrible feeling.
-About what?

323
00:25:29,745 --> 00:25:31,329
That we didn't do something.

324
00:25:32,331 --> 00:25:34,833
You feel that way
because we left in a hurry.

325
00:25:35,001 --> 00:25:38,253
-We took care of everything.
-Did I turn off the coffee?

326
00:25:38,629 --> 00:25:39,838
No.

327
00:25:40,006 --> 00:25:41,131
I did.

328
00:25:41,340 --> 00:25:42,757
Did you lock up?

329
00:25:44,135 --> 00:25:45,343
Yeah.

330
00:25:46,679 --> 00:25:48,054
Did you close the garage?

331
00:25:50,057 --> 00:25:51,141
That's it.

332
00:25:51,350 --> 00:25:53,768
I forgot to close the garage. That's it.

333
00:25:59,525 --> 00:26:01,401
No, that's not it.

334
00:26:03,446 --> 00:26:05,155
What else could we be forgetting?

335
00:26:09,076 --> 00:26:10,118
Kevin!

336
00:26:53,829 --> 00:26:56,998
The captain's doing all he can.
Your phones are out of order.

337
00:26:57,208 --> 00:26:59,668
We'll call when we land.
I'm sure it's okay.

338
00:27:01,629 --> 00:27:03,630
Horrible. Horrible.

339
00:27:03,964 --> 00:27:05,256
Just horrible.

340
00:27:05,675 --> 00:27:08,218
How could we do this? We forgot him.

341
00:27:08,427 --> 00:27:10,720
We didn't forget him,
we just miscounted.

342
00:27:11,806 --> 00:27:14,265
What kind of mother am I?

343
00:27:14,475 --> 00:27:17,936
If it makes you feel any better,
I forgot my reading glasses.

344
00:27:22,650 --> 00:27:25,527
Five families gone
on one block alone.

345
00:27:25,736 --> 00:27:28,697
They all told me
from their own mouths.

346
00:27:28,948 --> 00:27:30,448
It's almost too easy.

347
00:27:30,991 --> 00:27:32,033
Check it out:

348
00:27:32,243 --> 00:27:34,285
All the houses with nobody home...

349
00:27:34,495 --> 00:27:37,330
...have automatic timers
on their lights.

350
00:27:37,707 --> 00:27:41,000
But I got it all figured out.
Watch this.

351
00:27:42,253 --> 00:27:47,173
Number 664 will be going on
right about...

352
00:27:48,509 --> 00:27:49,759
...now.

353
00:27:50,761 --> 00:27:52,721
Wait, wait, wait.

354
00:27:53,806 --> 00:27:56,599
Number 672...

355
00:27:57,601 --> 00:28:00,145
...right now.

356
00:28:02,481 --> 00:28:03,565
Wait a minute.

357
00:28:03,858 --> 00:28:06,735
671...

358
00:28:06,902 --> 00:28:07,986
...now.

359
00:28:10,489 --> 00:28:13,992
And that's the one, Marvin.
That's the silver tuna.

360
00:28:14,493 --> 00:28:15,702
It's very G.

361
00:28:16,370 --> 00:28:18,788
Very G, huh? It's loaded.

362
00:28:18,998 --> 00:28:21,249
It's got lots of top-flight goods.

363
00:28:21,500 --> 00:28:24,794
-Stereos, VCRs--
-Toys?

364
00:28:25,004 --> 00:28:27,589
Probably looking at
some very fine jewelry.

365
00:28:28,007 --> 00:28:29,382
Possible cash horde.

366
00:28:30,134 --> 00:28:32,635
Odd marketable securities.

367
00:28:33,179 --> 00:28:35,597
Who knows? It's a gem.

368
00:28:36,390 --> 00:28:38,349
Grab your crowbar.

369
00:28:39,351 --> 00:28:41,019
Crowbars up.

370
00:29:40,204 --> 00:29:41,746
Which way?

371
00:29:41,914 --> 00:29:44,249
We'll go around back,
down the basement.

372
00:30:05,104 --> 00:30:07,897
-You said they were gone.
-They were gonna leave today.

373
00:30:08,107 --> 00:30:09,732
Let's get out of here.

374
00:30:46,186 --> 00:30:48,521
We have to use the phone, please.

375
00:30:49,356 --> 00:30:52,066
It's an emergency.
We really have to make a call.

376
00:30:52,276 --> 00:30:54,777
Please! Our brother's home alone.

377
00:30:55,487 --> 00:30:57,280
Give us the phone!

378
00:30:57,573 --> 00:30:58,781
I'm sorry. Thank you.

379
00:30:58,991 --> 00:31:01,701
I'm calling the police.
Book us a flight home.

380
00:31:01,911 --> 00:31:04,787
Get change out of here.
Call everybody you know.

381
00:31:04,997 --> 00:31:09,167
Here's my address book. You and Frank
call everyone on our street.

382
00:31:09,376 --> 00:31:11,169
Maybe somebody can help us.

383
00:31:11,378 --> 00:31:14,756
Hello? Hello?
Oh, she'll have to call you back.

384
00:31:21,180 --> 00:31:25,016
This is ridiculous. Only a wimp
would be hiding under a bed.

385
00:31:25,225 --> 00:31:29,228
And I can't be a wimp.
I'm the man of the house.

386
00:31:36,528 --> 00:31:39,864
Hey, I'm not afraid anymore!

387
00:31:40,908 --> 00:31:44,494
I said, I'm not afraid anymore!

388
00:31:45,037 --> 00:31:48,831
Do you hear me?
I'm not afraid anymore.

389
00:32:19,446 --> 00:32:20,738
Village police department.

390
00:32:20,906 --> 00:32:24,325
I'm calling from Paris.
I have a son who's home alone.

391
00:32:24,535 --> 00:32:29,622
I'd like somebody to go there. Tell him
that we're coming home to get him.

392
00:32:29,873 --> 00:32:31,916
Okay, let me connect you
with Family Crisis Intervention.

393
00:32:32,084 --> 00:32:33,418
No, it's not a family crisis.

394
00:32:33,585 --> 00:32:34,961
Hold on.

395
00:32:36,880 --> 00:32:40,258
Larry, can you pick up?
There's some hyper lady on hold.

396
00:32:40,509 --> 00:32:42,844
-What line, Rose?
-Two.

397
00:32:43,512 --> 00:32:45,888
Family Crisis Intervention,
Sergeant Balzak.

398
00:32:46,140 --> 00:32:48,975
I'm calling from Paris.
I have a son who's home alone.

399
00:32:49,184 --> 00:32:53,855
Has the child been involved in
violence with a drunk family member?

400
00:32:54,064 --> 00:32:55,106
No!

401
00:32:55,399 --> 00:32:57,900
Has he been involved
in a household accident?

402
00:32:58,110 --> 00:33:00,278
I don't know. I hope not.

403
00:33:01,655 --> 00:33:05,658
Has the child ingested any poison
or is an object lodged in his throat?

404
00:33:05,909 --> 00:33:09,370
No, he's home alone! I'd like
somebody to go over to the house...

405
00:33:09,580 --> 00:33:11,372
...and see if he's all right.

406
00:33:12,499 --> 00:33:16,085
You want us to go to your house,
just to check on him.

407
00:33:16,295 --> 00:33:17,378
Yes!

408
00:33:18,047 --> 00:33:19,630
Let me connect you to the police.

409
00:33:19,840 --> 00:33:21,299
They just transferred me.

410
00:33:21,467 --> 00:33:23,634
-Rose! Hyper on 2.
-Hang on.

411
00:33:23,844 --> 00:33:27,472
-Hold on, please.
-No, please don't hang up. Please!

412
00:33:28,307 --> 00:33:29,557
Any luck?

413
00:33:29,725 --> 00:33:31,142
No.

414
00:33:31,310 --> 00:33:33,978
-I couldn't get anybody.
-Leslie?

415
00:33:34,188 --> 00:33:36,481
Nothing but a bunch
of answering machines.

416
00:33:38,650 --> 00:33:41,611
Somebody pick up. Pick up!

417
00:33:41,820 --> 00:33:43,821
Oh, hi, ma'am. It's you again.

418
00:33:43,989 --> 00:33:47,950
I'm calling from Paris.
I have a son who's home alone, and I--

419
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:51,954
We'll send a policeman over
to your house to check on your son.

420
00:34:22,236 --> 00:34:24,904
There's no one home.
The house looks secure.

421
00:34:25,114 --> 00:34:27,198
Tell them to count their kids again.

422
00:34:28,283 --> 00:34:30,701
You can't bump somebody or ask or--?

423
00:34:30,911 --> 00:34:32,745
There's no way I can do that.

424
00:34:32,955 --> 00:34:35,039
Isn't there a way
if you ask somebody?

425
00:34:35,249 --> 00:34:36,749
If you said it's an emergency--

426
00:34:36,959 --> 00:34:38,209
I cannot ask them.

427
00:34:38,502 --> 00:34:40,753
A policeman's going
over to the house.

428
00:34:40,963 --> 00:34:43,881
Well, that's a relief.
Everything here is booked.

429
00:34:44,049 --> 00:34:45,133
Nothing to Chicago?

430
00:34:45,384 --> 00:34:48,553
There's nothing to Chicago,
New York, Nashville.

431
00:34:49,930 --> 00:34:53,057
-What about a private plane?
-Sorry. We don't do that.

432
00:34:53,308 --> 00:34:56,185
The only thing is a booking
for us on Friday morning.

433
00:34:56,395 --> 00:34:58,896
Friday morn-- That's two days away.

434
00:34:59,106 --> 00:35:02,817
The kids are exhausted and so are you.
There's nothing we can do.

435
00:35:03,026 --> 00:35:08,030
I say we go over to Rob's, and
that way we can call the police again.

436
00:35:08,323 --> 00:35:11,534
I'm not leaving here
unless it's on an airplane.

437
00:35:11,743 --> 00:35:13,828
Madame, we are doing
everything we can.

438
00:35:14,079 --> 00:35:18,040
If you want to stay at the airport,
maybe we can get you on standby.

439
00:35:18,292 --> 00:35:21,169
It is a possibility
that a seat will open up.

440
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:24,714
-Is that okay?
-Yes. I'll wait.

441
00:35:30,470 --> 00:35:32,680
-Bye. I'll miss you, honey.
-Bye.

442
00:35:36,685 --> 00:35:38,436
Don't you get lost.

443
00:35:40,022 --> 00:35:41,189
Goodbye.

444
00:35:56,955 --> 00:36:00,041
I took a shower, washing every
body part with actual soap.

445
00:36:00,334 --> 00:36:02,168
Including all my major crevices...

446
00:36:02,377 --> 00:36:04,795
...between my toes
and in my belly button...

447
00:36:05,047 --> 00:36:07,465
...which I never did before
but enjoyed.

448
00:36:07,966 --> 00:36:13,054
I washed my hair with adult formula
shampoo and used cream rinse.

449
00:36:14,056 --> 00:36:17,308
I can't find my toothbrush,
so I'll pick one up today.

450
00:36:17,559 --> 00:36:19,644
Other than that, I'm in good shape.

451
00:37:10,279 --> 00:37:13,531
All right! Buzz's life savings.

452
00:37:40,350 --> 00:37:42,977
I thought the Murphys went to Florida.

453
00:37:59,244 --> 00:38:02,288
You're one of the great
cat burglars of the world.

454
00:38:02,497 --> 00:38:05,166
You think you can keep it
down a little in there?

455
00:38:05,834 --> 00:38:09,587
You've reached the Murphys.
Please leave a message after the beep.

456
00:38:10,464 --> 00:38:14,342
This is Peter McCallister again.
We're in Paris at my brother's.

457
00:38:14,593 --> 00:38:18,012
Let me give you the number here.
The country code is 33.

458
00:38:18,221 --> 00:38:23,184
The area code is 14
and the number is 694-876--

459
00:38:23,602 --> 00:38:25,394
-Hey, Harry.
-Yeah?

460
00:38:25,645 --> 00:38:28,481
That house we ran last night,
was that the McCallister's?

461
00:38:28,648 --> 00:38:30,149
Yeah.

462
00:38:30,484 --> 00:38:33,819
-Call me in Paris.
-You're right. They're gone.

463
00:38:37,240 --> 00:38:40,785
-I knew they were.
-Silver tuna tonight.

464
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:51,253
How may I help you?

465
00:38:51,922 --> 00:38:55,216
Is this toothbrush approved
by the American Dental Association?

466
00:38:56,009 --> 00:38:57,551
Well, I don't know.

467
00:38:58,637 --> 00:39:02,056
-It doesn't say, hon.
-Can you please find out?

468
00:39:05,227 --> 00:39:06,936
-Herb.
-Yeah?

469
00:39:07,145 --> 00:39:10,398
I got a question here
about a toothbrush.

470
00:39:16,988 --> 00:39:21,492
Do you know, is this brush approved
by the American Dental Association?

471
00:39:21,660 --> 00:39:22,827
I don't know.

472
00:39:45,308 --> 00:39:47,726
Oh, hon, you pay for that here.

473
00:39:49,813 --> 00:39:51,689
Wait, you have to pay for that.

474
00:39:52,441 --> 00:39:55,526
Son! Son! Hey!

475
00:39:55,986 --> 00:39:58,446
Jimmy, stop that boy!

476
00:40:02,868 --> 00:40:04,034
Hey!

477
00:40:04,244 --> 00:40:06,120
Hey!

478
00:40:08,373 --> 00:40:09,874
Shoplifter!

479
00:40:13,712 --> 00:40:14,920
Hey! Hey, kid!

480
00:40:21,928 --> 00:40:23,304
Come back here!

481
00:40:24,806 --> 00:40:26,474
Stop it, will you?

482
00:40:27,017 --> 00:40:28,142
Come here.

483
00:41:06,306 --> 00:41:08,182
I'm a criminal.

484
00:41:35,502 --> 00:41:37,211
What's so funny?

485
00:41:38,004 --> 00:41:39,296
What's so funny?

486
00:41:39,798 --> 00:41:40,923
Why are you laughing?

487
00:41:44,219 --> 00:41:45,427
You did it again.

488
00:41:46,846 --> 00:41:48,305
You left the water running.

489
00:41:49,224 --> 00:41:51,642
Why do you do that?
I told you not to do it.

490
00:41:51,851 --> 00:41:54,228
-It's our calling card.
-Calling card.

491
00:41:54,437 --> 00:41:56,564
All the great ones leave their mark.

492
00:41:56,815 --> 00:41:58,399
We're the Wet Bandits.

493
00:41:58,817 --> 00:42:01,360
You're sick, you know?
You're really sick.

494
00:42:02,237 --> 00:42:04,029
-I'm not sick.
-Yes, you are.

495
00:42:04,239 --> 00:42:05,447
It's a sick thing to do.

496
00:42:12,247 --> 00:42:14,081
-We don't need that.
-Don't tell me--

497
00:42:14,332 --> 00:42:16,166
I can do it if I want to.

498
00:42:18,336 --> 00:42:20,546
It's not sick. Hey, watch out!

499
00:42:28,847 --> 00:42:30,180
Hey! Hey!

500
00:42:30,390 --> 00:42:32,349
You gotta watch out for traffic.

501
00:42:32,726 --> 00:42:34,643
-Sorry.
-Damn.

502
00:42:34,853 --> 00:42:37,229
Santy don't visit
the funeral homes, buddy.

503
00:42:38,273 --> 00:42:39,481
Okay, okay.

504
00:42:40,358 --> 00:42:42,443
Merry Christmas.

505
00:42:52,621 --> 00:42:53,954
What's the matter?

506
00:42:54,372 --> 00:42:56,498
I don't like the way
that kid looked at me.

507
00:42:56,708 --> 00:43:00,294
-Ever seen him before?
-I saw a hundred kids this week.

508
00:43:01,379 --> 00:43:03,172
Let's see what house he goes into.

509
00:43:35,747 --> 00:43:37,081
Why's he going faster?

510
00:43:37,332 --> 00:43:39,416
I told you something's wrong.

511
00:43:39,626 --> 00:43:41,627
He looked at me weird.
Why would he run?

512
00:44:17,789 --> 00:44:19,540
Maybe he went in the church.

513
00:44:19,833 --> 00:44:22,543
-I'm not going in there.
-Me neither.

514
00:44:22,836 --> 00:44:24,670
Let's get out of here.

515
00:44:42,564 --> 00:44:46,191
When those guys come back,
I'll be ready.

516
00:45:11,009 --> 00:45:12,259
Did they come back?

517
00:45:12,719 --> 00:45:14,553
From Paris?

518
00:45:50,173 --> 00:45:52,549
We'll come back tomorrow.
Maybe they'll be gone.

519
00:45:53,301 --> 00:45:56,053
We better go before
somebody sees us.

520
00:46:27,585 --> 00:46:29,419
Look what I found in the kitchen.

521
00:46:29,671 --> 00:46:31,797
Frank, those are for later.

522
00:46:36,594 --> 00:46:39,012
Do you want a little shrimp, huh?

523
00:46:40,139 --> 00:46:41,849
Do you speak English?

524
00:46:45,395 --> 00:46:46,728
Well, is there--?

525
00:46:52,527 --> 00:46:55,737
-Did you get anybody?
-I am looking for my son!

526
00:46:55,947 --> 00:46:57,656
No, I can't find anybody.

527
00:46:57,866 --> 00:47:00,951
They're all shopping.
Nobody's home for the holidays.

528
00:47:01,202 --> 00:47:02,870
Never mind, forget it.

529
00:47:03,746 --> 00:47:06,456
-This is so pointless.
-What?

530
00:47:06,833 --> 00:47:08,917
We're here rotting in this apartment.

531
00:47:09,127 --> 00:47:11,336
Kevin's at home.
Mom's at the airport.

532
00:47:11,713 --> 00:47:14,298
-So?
-You're not worried about Kevin?

533
00:47:14,507 --> 00:47:19,386
Why should I be? He acted like a jerk,
and now he caught it in the butt.

534
00:47:20,638 --> 00:47:24,016
He's so little and helpless.
Don't you think he's flipped out?

535
00:47:24,225 --> 00:47:27,311
The trout can use a couple of days
in the real world.

536
00:47:27,520 --> 00:47:29,730
You're not worried
something might happen?

537
00:47:30,648 --> 00:47:32,524
No. For three reasons:

538
00:47:32,734 --> 00:47:37,404
A, I'm not that lucky.
Two, we have smoke detectors...

539
00:47:37,655 --> 00:47:41,491
...and D, we live in the most boring
street in the United States...

540
00:47:41,701 --> 00:47:46,079
...where nothing even remotely
dangerous will ever happen. Period.

541
00:48:13,191 --> 00:48:14,232
Who is it?

542
00:48:14,400 --> 00:48:16,610
It's Little Nero's. I have your pizza.

543
00:48:17,236 --> 00:48:19,905
Leave it on the doorstep
and get the hell out.

544
00:48:20,865 --> 00:48:22,282
Okay.

545
00:48:23,701 --> 00:48:25,077
What about the money?

546
00:48:26,454 --> 00:48:27,955
What money?

547
00:48:28,748 --> 00:48:31,416
Well, you have to pay
for your pizza, sir.

548
00:48:32,377 --> 00:48:35,754
Is that a fact?
How much do I owe you?

549
00:48:37,256 --> 00:48:39,091
That'll be $11.80, sir.

550
00:48:46,557 --> 00:48:49,142
Keep the change, you filthy animal.

551
00:48:51,062 --> 00:48:52,813
-Cheapskate.
-Hey.

552
00:48:53,022 --> 00:48:55,315
I'm gonna give you
to the count of 10...

553
00:48:55,525 --> 00:48:57,901
...to get your ugly, yellow...

554
00:48:58,152 --> 00:49:00,237
...no-good keister off my property...

555
00:49:00,446 --> 00:49:02,572
...before I pump your guts full of lead.

556
00:49:02,782 --> 00:49:05,534
One, two...10.

557
00:49:33,521 --> 00:49:36,857
A lovely cheese pizza, just for me.

558
00:49:40,069 --> 00:49:41,653
--to Dallas/Fort Worth.

559
00:49:41,904 --> 00:49:43,697
American Airlines....

560
00:49:45,450 --> 00:49:47,993
So we have the $500,
the pocket translator...

561
00:49:48,202 --> 00:49:50,537
...the two first-class seats,
that's an upgrade--

562
00:49:50,788 --> 00:49:51,913
Is that a real Rolex?

563
00:49:53,666 --> 00:49:55,959
-Do you think it is?
-No.

564
00:49:56,169 --> 00:49:59,379
But who can tell? I also have a ring.

565
00:49:59,630 --> 00:50:01,465
That is beautiful!

566
00:50:01,674 --> 00:50:03,008
They're boarding.

567
00:50:03,634 --> 00:50:06,845
She's offered us two first-class
tickets if we go Friday.

568
00:50:07,055 --> 00:50:11,308
Plus a ring, a watch,
a pocket translator, $500 and--

569
00:50:11,517 --> 00:50:12,809
The earrings.

570
00:50:13,102 --> 00:50:16,855
She's got her own earrings.
A whole shoebox full of them.

571
00:50:17,065 --> 00:50:18,648
-Come on, come on.
-No, but--

572
00:50:20,068 --> 00:50:21,109
I'm desperate.

573
00:50:22,236 --> 00:50:25,989
I'm begging you.
From a mother to a mother. Please!

574
00:50:28,117 --> 00:50:30,827
-Oh, Ed.
-Please!

575
00:50:31,829 --> 00:50:33,497
Oh, all right.

576
00:50:39,253 --> 00:50:41,338
"Dear Santa, I got a sister last year.

577
00:50:41,506 --> 00:50:43,465
This year I'd rather have Clay-Doh."

578
00:50:58,439 --> 00:50:59,481
I didn't mean it.

579
00:50:59,690 --> 00:51:02,859
If you come back, I'll never
be a pain in the butt again.

580
00:51:03,194 --> 00:51:06,363
I promise. Good night.

581
00:52:47,548 --> 00:52:49,466
Are those microwave dinners good?

582
00:52:50,092 --> 00:52:52,844
-I don't know.
-I'll give them a whirl.

583
00:52:58,351 --> 00:52:59,893
For the kids.

584
00:53:02,271 --> 00:53:04,397
Hold on, I got a coupon for that.

585
00:53:05,733 --> 00:53:07,609
It was in the paper this morning.

586
00:53:11,239 --> 00:53:12,280
$19.83.

587
00:53:12,907 --> 00:53:14,157
Okay.

588
00:53:18,246 --> 00:53:19,663
Are you here by yourself?

589
00:53:21,082 --> 00:53:22,749
Ma'am, I'm 8 years old.

590
00:53:23,000 --> 00:53:27,212
You think I'd be here alone?
I don't think so.

591
00:53:27,922 --> 00:53:29,005
Where's your mom?

592
00:53:29,215 --> 00:53:30,799
-In the car.
-Where's your dad?

593
00:53:31,008 --> 00:53:33,927
-He's at work.
-What about brothers and sisters?

594
00:53:34,136 --> 00:53:35,512
I'm an only child.

595
00:53:36,013 --> 00:53:38,098
-Where do you live?
-I can't tell you.

596
00:53:38,307 --> 00:53:41,184
-Why not?
-Because you're a stranger.

597
00:54:19,724 --> 00:54:23,101
Hello, Kevin!

598
00:54:26,564 --> 00:54:27,814
Shut up!

599
00:54:41,370 --> 00:54:42,620
I don't get it.

600
00:54:43,247 --> 00:54:45,415
It looks like there's nobody's home.

601
00:54:46,417 --> 00:54:48,626
Last night the place is jumping.

602
00:54:49,253 --> 00:54:51,129
Something ain't right.

603
00:54:51,881 --> 00:54:52,922
Go check it out.

604
00:55:01,932 --> 00:55:03,099
Now?

605
00:55:03,517 --> 00:55:06,978
No, tomorrow, egghead!
Now! Go ahead.

606
00:55:09,315 --> 00:55:10,482
"Now?"

607
00:55:27,833 --> 00:55:28,958
Shit!

608
00:55:32,254 --> 00:55:33,838
Get the hell out of here.

609
00:55:34,048 --> 00:55:37,133
All right, Johnny.
But what about my money?

610
00:55:37,301 --> 00:55:38,426
What money?

611
00:55:38,636 --> 00:55:40,845
A.C. said you had
some dough for me.

612
00:55:41,055 --> 00:55:43,932
Is that a fact?
How much do I owe you?

613
00:55:44,141 --> 00:55:45,934
A.C. said 10 percent.

614
00:55:47,186 --> 00:55:49,687
Too bad A.C. ain't in charge no more.

615
00:55:49,897 --> 00:55:51,064
What do you mean?

616
00:55:51,273 --> 00:55:53,775
He's upstairs, taking a bath.

617
00:55:54,693 --> 00:55:56,861
He'll call you when he gets out.

618
00:55:58,322 --> 00:56:02,409
Hey, I tell you what
I'm gonna give you, Snakes.

619
00:56:03,244 --> 00:56:06,329
-Snakes?
-I'll give you to the count of 10...

620
00:56:06,539 --> 00:56:08,748
...to get your ugly,
yellow, no-good...

621
00:56:08,958 --> 00:56:10,917
...keister off my property...

622
00:56:11,168 --> 00:56:13,169
...before I pump your guts full of lead.

623
00:56:13,421 --> 00:56:16,047
All right, Johnny. I'm sorry. I'm going.

624
00:56:16,257 --> 00:56:19,175
One, two...10.

625
00:56:38,404 --> 00:56:41,364
Keep the change, you filthy animal.

626
00:56:46,203 --> 00:56:47,245
What happened?

627
00:56:47,413 --> 00:56:49,956
I don't know who,
but somebody got blown away.

628
00:56:50,207 --> 00:56:52,459
Somebody beat us, they're in there.

629
00:56:52,710 --> 00:56:53,793
Two of them.

630
00:56:54,044 --> 00:56:56,629
There was arguing.
One blew the other one away.

631
00:56:56,839 --> 00:56:58,423
-Who?
-I don't know.

632
00:56:59,258 --> 00:57:04,345
I recognized one of their voices.
I heard that name "Snakes" before.

633
00:57:04,597 --> 00:57:08,266
Snakes? Snakes. Snakes.
I don't know no Snakes.

634
00:57:08,476 --> 00:57:11,728
Snakes. Let's get out of here.

635
00:57:14,106 --> 00:57:15,356
Hold it. Hold it.

636
00:57:15,566 --> 00:57:18,902
Let's wait and see who it is.
We work this neighborhood too.

637
00:57:19,820 --> 00:57:21,738
Suppose the cops finger us for a job...

638
00:57:21,947 --> 00:57:24,908
...and they ask us
about a murder in the area.

639
00:57:25,117 --> 00:57:28,077
Won't it be nice to have
a face to go with it?

640
00:57:30,789 --> 00:57:31,915
That's a good idea.

641
00:57:32,458 --> 00:57:35,502
Of course it's a good idea. Snakes?

642
00:57:35,753 --> 00:57:37,921
He sounded like a snake.

643
00:57:44,512 --> 00:57:45,678
Everything's full.

644
00:57:45,888 --> 00:57:47,388
Everything's full?

645
00:57:47,598 --> 00:57:50,433
I'm very sorry,
but it is Christmas Eve.

646
00:57:51,185 --> 00:57:52,977
What about another airline?

647
00:57:57,650 --> 00:58:00,443
Nothing available.
May I help you get a hotel room?

648
00:58:00,653 --> 00:58:04,197
-Tomorrow we can get you a flight.
-I can't wait that long.

649
00:58:04,823 --> 00:58:08,701
I'm sorry, ma'am, but we're doing
absolutely everything we can.

650
00:58:12,957 --> 00:58:15,917
I'm in your way. I'm sorry.
You've places to go.

651
00:58:16,126 --> 00:58:18,503
Got a ticket there, good. Excuse me.

652
00:58:18,796 --> 00:58:23,550
Look, I have been awake for almost
60 hours. I'm tired and I'm dirty.

653
00:58:24,051 --> 00:58:28,096
I have been from Chicago to Paris,
to Dallas to-- Where am I?

654
00:58:28,722 --> 00:58:30,139
Scranton.

655
00:58:30,432 --> 00:58:32,976
I'm trying to get home
to my 8-year-old son.

656
00:58:33,936 --> 00:58:36,312
Now you're telling me it's hopeless?

657
00:58:36,480 --> 00:58:38,982
-I'm sorry.
-No. No way.

658
00:58:39,233 --> 00:58:42,235
This is Christmas!
The season of perpetual hope.

659
00:58:43,320 --> 00:58:46,072
If I have to get on
your runway and hitchhike...

660
00:58:46,323 --> 00:58:48,324
...if it costs me everything I own...

661
00:58:48,534 --> 00:58:51,369
...if I have to sell my soul
to the devil himself...

662
00:58:51,579 --> 00:58:54,372
...I am going to get home to my son.

663
00:58:55,666 --> 00:58:57,709
Ma'am, if there was anything--

664
00:58:57,918 --> 00:58:59,502
Do it. Do anything.

665
00:58:59,712 --> 00:59:01,629
-I can get you a hotel room.
-What?

666
00:59:01,922 --> 00:59:05,925
Can you excuse us for a sec?
Can I see you for a second, please?

667
00:59:06,135 --> 00:59:08,011
Excuse us.

668
00:59:10,097 --> 00:59:12,515
You got a little bit of a dilemma.

669
00:59:12,725 --> 00:59:15,143
We got a crisis ourselves.

670
00:59:15,728 --> 00:59:17,979
Allow me to introduce myself.
Gus Polinski.

671
00:59:20,399 --> 00:59:22,609
Polka King of the Midwest?

672
00:59:25,863 --> 00:59:27,363
The Kenosha Kickers?

673
00:59:28,657 --> 00:59:29,991
-Hi there.
-Hi.

674
00:59:30,868 --> 00:59:34,245
That's okay. I thought
you might have recognized--

675
00:59:34,496 --> 00:59:37,957
I had a few hits a few years ago.
That's why I just--

676
00:59:38,125 --> 00:59:39,375
"Polka, Polka, Polka"?

677
00:59:41,920 --> 00:59:44,172
No? "Twin Lakes Polka"?

678
00:59:44,381 --> 00:59:49,218
"Yamahoozie Polka," a.k.a.
"Kiss Me Polka"? "Polka Twist"?

679
00:59:49,428 --> 00:59:50,887
These are songs?

680
00:59:51,096 --> 00:59:53,973
Yeah. Yeah, we--
Some fairly big hits for us.

681
00:59:54,224 --> 00:59:56,017
You know, in the early '70s.

682
00:59:56,226 --> 00:59:59,020
Yeah, we sold about
623 copies of that.

683
00:59:59,229 --> 01:00:00,813
-In Chicago?
-No, Sheboygan.

684
01:00:01,023 --> 01:00:02,690
Very big in Sheboygan.

685
01:00:02,900 --> 01:00:04,400
Did you say you could help?

686
01:00:04,568 --> 01:00:08,321
Anyway, I'm rambling on here.
Our flight was canceled...

687
01:00:08,530 --> 01:00:12,909
...so we gotta drive. See the guy
in the yellow jacket over there?

688
01:00:13,118 --> 01:00:16,537
He's gonna rent us a nice big van
to drive to Milwaukee.

689
01:00:16,747 --> 01:00:20,083
Now, I heard you had some problems
getting to Chicago?

690
01:00:20,459 --> 01:00:21,709
To see your kid?

691
01:00:21,960 --> 01:00:25,922
My son. He--
We left, and he's there.

692
01:00:26,090 --> 01:00:29,717
If you have to get to Chicago,
we'll gladly drive you.

693
01:00:29,927 --> 01:00:32,011
It's on the way to Milwaukee.

694
01:00:32,513 --> 01:00:34,931
-You'd give me a ride?
-Sure, why not?

695
01:00:35,140 --> 01:00:36,641
You gotta get home.

696
01:00:36,850 --> 01:00:39,852
-A ride to Chicago?
-Sure, it's Christmastime.

697
01:00:40,479 --> 01:00:42,063
Thank you. Oh, thank you.

698
01:00:42,314 --> 01:00:44,440
You don't mind
going with polka bums?

699
01:00:44,650 --> 01:00:46,442
No, I'd love to.

700
01:01:08,966 --> 01:01:11,467
Hey, Marv. Marv, Marv!

701
01:01:11,677 --> 01:01:13,511
Look at this.

702
01:01:19,476 --> 01:01:23,062
I think we're getting scammed
by a kindergartner.

703
01:01:53,427 --> 01:01:55,678
Dad, can you come here
and help me?

704
01:02:00,434 --> 01:02:02,810
Remember that kid
we saw the other day?

705
01:02:03,771 --> 01:02:05,271
He lives here.

706
01:02:05,606 --> 01:02:08,065
If the kid's here,
the parents got to be.

707
01:02:08,692 --> 01:02:10,067
He's home alone.

708
01:02:18,327 --> 01:02:20,453
What? You want to
come back tonight?

709
01:02:20,662 --> 01:02:22,038
Even with the kid here?

710
01:02:22,289 --> 01:02:24,415
I don't think that's a good idea.

711
01:02:24,625 --> 01:02:27,335
That house is the reason
we worked this block.

712
01:02:27,586 --> 01:02:29,837
Ever since I saw that house,
I wanted it.

713
01:02:30,255 --> 01:02:32,215
Let's take it one step at a time.

714
01:02:32,424 --> 01:02:36,969
We'll unload the van, get a bite
to eat, we'll come back about 9:00.

715
01:02:37,262 --> 01:02:38,471
Nine o'clock.

716
01:02:38,680 --> 01:02:39,972
This way it's dark.

717
01:02:40,557 --> 01:02:43,267
Yeah, kids are scared of the dark.

718
01:02:43,477 --> 01:02:46,145
You're afraid of the dark too.
You know you are.

719
01:02:47,648 --> 01:02:48,981
No, I'm not.

720
01:02:49,191 --> 01:02:51,067
-Yes, you are.
-Not, not, not.

721
01:02:51,276 --> 01:02:52,443
You are so.

722
01:02:52,653 --> 01:02:54,654
Mom, where are you?

723
01:03:09,378 --> 01:03:10,628
Do you play?

724
01:03:11,296 --> 01:03:14,632
Do you want to try?
Go ahead, try it. Try it!

725
01:03:42,369 --> 01:03:44,453
-Excuse me.
-Yeah?

726
01:03:46,123 --> 01:03:47,707
Hey, nice shoes.

727
01:03:48,166 --> 01:03:49,667
Oh, thanks.

728
01:03:49,877 --> 01:03:53,337
Is he still here?
It's really important that I see him.

729
01:03:54,131 --> 01:03:57,508
He's getting in his car.
If you hurry, you can catch him.

730
01:03:58,886 --> 01:04:03,222
How low! Giving Kriss Kringle
a parking ticket on Christmas Eve!

731
01:04:03,432 --> 01:04:06,017
What's next, rabies shots
for the Easter Bunny?

732
01:04:06,226 --> 01:04:07,727
Santa, hold on.

733
01:04:10,063 --> 01:04:13,858
-Can I talk to you?
-Make it quick. Santa's running late.

734
01:04:14,151 --> 01:04:16,485
I know you're not
the real Santa Claus.

735
01:04:16,987 --> 01:04:20,448
What makes you say that?
Just out of curiosity.

736
01:04:20,657 --> 01:04:24,160
-I'm old enough to know how it works.
-All right.

737
01:04:24,328 --> 01:04:26,370
But I also know you work for him.

738
01:04:26,705 --> 01:04:29,540
-I'd like you to give him a message.
-Shoot.

739
01:04:30,000 --> 01:04:34,754
Kevin McCallister, 671 Lincoln Blvd.
Do you need the phone number?

740
01:04:35,088 --> 01:04:36,339
No, that's all right.

741
01:04:36,715 --> 01:04:38,466
This is extremely important.

742
01:04:38,717 --> 01:04:43,721
Please tell him instead of presents,
I just want my family back.

743
01:04:44,264 --> 01:04:48,684
No toys. Nothing but Peter, Kate,
Buzz, Megan, Linnie and Jeff.

744
01:04:48,894 --> 01:04:50,937
And my aunt and my cousins.

745
01:04:51,188 --> 01:04:54,273
And if he has time,
my Uncle Frank. Okay?

746
01:04:55,984 --> 01:04:57,193
Okay.

747
01:04:58,070 --> 01:05:00,363
-I'll see what I can do.
-Thanks.

748
01:05:00,572 --> 01:05:05,117
Wait. My elf took the last of the
candy canes home to her boyfriend.

749
01:05:05,410 --> 01:05:07,203
-That's okay.
-No, don't be silly.

750
01:05:07,412 --> 01:05:10,289
Everybody who sees Santa
has gotta get something.

751
01:05:10,499 --> 01:05:14,627
Here, hold out your little paw there.
There you go.

752
01:05:15,128 --> 01:05:17,463
-Don't spoil your dinner.
-I won't.

753
01:05:17,881 --> 01:05:19,298
Thanks.

754
01:05:30,519 --> 01:05:32,103
Son of a--!

755
01:08:29,489 --> 01:08:30,823
Merry Christmas.

756
01:08:33,410 --> 01:08:34,618
May I sit down?

757
01:08:46,006 --> 01:08:47,339
That's my granddaughter.

758
01:08:48,008 --> 01:08:49,925
The little red-haired girl.

759
01:08:51,928 --> 01:08:54,680
She's about your age. You know her?

760
01:08:54,848 --> 01:08:55,973
No.

761
01:08:56,183 --> 01:08:59,226
-You live next to me, don't you?
-Yeah.

762
01:08:59,436 --> 01:09:02,980
You can say hello when you see me.
You don't have to be afraid.

763
01:09:03,982 --> 01:09:08,944
There's a lot of things going around
about me, but none of it's true. Okay?

764
01:09:09,779 --> 01:09:11,780
-You've been good this year?
-I think so.

765
01:09:12,449 --> 01:09:13,782
You swear to it?

766
01:09:14,159 --> 01:09:15,201
No.

767
01:09:15,452 --> 01:09:20,039
Yeah. Well, this is the place to be
if you're feeling bad about yourself.

768
01:09:20,457 --> 01:09:23,083
-It is?
-I think so.

769
01:09:23,293 --> 01:09:25,878
-Are you feeling bad about yourself?
-No.

770
01:09:30,342 --> 01:09:34,845
I've been kind of a pain lately.
I said some things I shouldn't have.

771
01:09:35,597 --> 01:09:38,265
I really haven't been
too good this year.

772
01:09:38,892 --> 01:09:39,934
Yeah.

773
01:09:40,101 --> 01:09:43,354
I'm kind of upset
because I really like my family.

774
01:09:43,563 --> 01:09:48,484
Even though sometimes I say I don't.
Sometimes I even think I don't.

775
01:09:48,777 --> 01:09:51,528
-Do you get that?
-I think so.

776
01:09:51,988 --> 01:09:54,823
How you feel about your family
is a complicated thing.

777
01:09:55,075 --> 01:09:57,493
Especially with an older brother.

778
01:09:58,245 --> 01:10:00,579
Deep down, you'll always love them.

779
01:10:00,789 --> 01:10:05,084
But you can forget that you love them.
You can hurt them, they can hurt you.

780
01:10:05,293 --> 01:10:07,711
And that's not just
because you're young.

781
01:10:09,422 --> 01:10:12,132
You want to know the real
reason why I'm here?

782
01:10:12,342 --> 01:10:13,592
Sure.

783
01:10:14,052 --> 01:10:17,846
I came to hear my granddaughter sing.
I can't come hear her tonight.

784
01:10:18,431 --> 01:10:19,515
You have plans?

785
01:10:19,933 --> 01:10:21,767
No.

786
01:10:21,935 --> 01:10:23,269
I'm not welcome.

787
01:10:24,062 --> 01:10:25,271
At church?

788
01:10:25,522 --> 01:10:27,606
You're always welcome at church.

789
01:10:27,816 --> 01:10:29,900
I'm not welcome with my son.

790
01:10:31,361 --> 01:10:35,114
Years back, before you and your family
moved on the block...

791
01:10:35,865 --> 01:10:37,533
...I had an argument with my son.

792
01:10:38,326 --> 01:10:39,368
How old is he?

793
01:10:39,703 --> 01:10:41,245
He's grown up.

794
01:10:42,622 --> 01:10:47,293
We lost our tempers, and I said
I didn't care to see him anymore.

795
01:10:47,794 --> 01:10:52,131
He said the same, and we haven't
spoken to each other since.

796
01:10:53,300 --> 01:10:55,551
If you miss him,
why don't you call him?

797
01:10:56,177 --> 01:10:58,304
I'm afraid if I call,
he won't talk to me.

798
01:10:58,555 --> 01:11:00,055
How do you know?

799
01:11:01,057 --> 01:11:03,726
I don't know.
I'm just afraid he won't.

800
01:11:04,561 --> 01:11:07,563
No offense, but aren't you
a little old to be afraid?

801
01:11:08,940 --> 01:11:11,108
You can be old for a lot of things.

802
01:11:11,318 --> 01:11:14,111
-You're never too old to be afraid.
-That's true.

803
01:11:14,321 --> 01:11:16,238
I was afraid of our basement.

804
01:11:16,448 --> 01:11:19,742
It's dark. There's weird stuff
down there, and it smells funny.

805
01:11:19,951 --> 01:11:23,412
That sort of thing.
It's bothered me for years.

806
01:11:23,788 --> 01:11:24,955
Basements are like that.

807
01:11:26,291 --> 01:11:28,667
I made myself go down
to do some laundry...

808
01:11:28,877 --> 01:11:31,003
...and I found out it's not so bad.

809
01:11:31,254 --> 01:11:35,841
I worried about it, but if you
turn on the lights, it's no big deal.

810
01:11:36,134 --> 01:11:37,176
What's your point?

811
01:11:37,635 --> 01:11:40,387
My point is,
you should call your son.

812
01:11:41,348 --> 01:11:44,099
-What if he won't talk to me?
-At least you'll know.

813
01:11:44,309 --> 01:11:48,687
Then you could stop worrying about it.
You won't have to be afraid anymore.

814
01:11:49,356 --> 01:11:54,401
No matter how mad I was, I'd talk to
my dad. Especially around the holidays.

815
01:11:56,154 --> 01:11:57,738
I don't know.

816
01:11:57,947 --> 01:12:00,866
Just give it a shot.
For your granddaughter anyway.

817
01:12:01,117 --> 01:12:04,286
I'm sure she misses you.
And the presents.

818
01:12:04,996 --> 01:12:06,330
I send her a check.

819
01:12:07,040 --> 01:12:10,626
I wish my grandparents did that.
They always send me clothes.

820
01:12:10,835 --> 01:12:13,670
Last year I got a sweater
with a bird knitted on it.

821
01:12:13,922 --> 01:12:14,963
Oh, that's nice.

822
01:12:15,173 --> 01:12:17,299
Not for a guy in the second grade.

823
01:12:17,509 --> 01:12:20,135
You can get beat up
for wearing something like that.

824
01:12:21,513 --> 01:12:23,555
I have a friend who got nailed...

825
01:12:23,765 --> 01:12:26,642
...because there was a rumor
he wore dinosaur pajamas.

826
01:12:27,769 --> 01:12:32,022
You better run home where you belong.
Think about what I said.

827
01:12:32,440 --> 01:12:33,816
-All right?
-Okay.

828
01:12:34,609 --> 01:12:35,776
It's nice talking to you.

829
01:12:36,945 --> 01:12:38,695
Nice talking to you.

830
01:12:44,953 --> 01:12:47,037
-What about you?
-Me?

831
01:12:47,705 --> 01:12:49,206
Yeah. You and your son.

832
01:12:51,167 --> 01:12:53,043
We'll see what happens.

833
01:12:54,337 --> 01:12:55,587
Merry Christmas.

834
01:12:56,798 --> 01:12:58,715
Merry Christmas.

835
01:13:50,602 --> 01:13:54,229
This is my house. I have to defend it.

836
01:15:22,068 --> 01:15:25,320
We'll check it out.
We can come back for the truck.

837
01:15:33,580 --> 01:15:34,705
How do we go in?

838
01:15:35,331 --> 01:15:38,250
We'll go to the back door.
Maybe he'll let us in.

839
01:15:38,459 --> 01:15:41,837
Yeah, he's a kid. Kids are stupid.

840
01:15:43,881 --> 01:15:47,843
Bless this nutritious, microwaveable
macaroni and cheese dinner...

841
01:15:48,052 --> 01:15:50,846
...and the people
who sold it on sale. Amen.

842
01:16:15,913 --> 01:16:18,582
This is it. Don't get scared now.

843
01:16:31,804 --> 01:16:34,473
Merry Christmas, little fella.

844
01:16:35,391 --> 01:16:40,062
We know that you're in there
and that you're all alone.

845
01:16:40,605 --> 01:16:42,898
Yeah, come on, kid. Open up.

846
01:16:43,816 --> 01:16:46,443
It's Santy Claus and his elf.

847
01:16:48,905 --> 01:16:50,113
We won't hurt you.

848
01:16:50,782 --> 01:16:54,201
No, no. Got some nice
presents for you.

849
01:16:54,535 --> 01:16:58,205
Be a good little fella now
and open the door.

850
01:17:03,044 --> 01:17:04,169
What?

851
01:17:06,005 --> 01:17:08,006
What? What?

852
01:17:08,716 --> 01:17:09,758
What?

853
01:17:09,926 --> 01:17:12,427
-What happened?
-Get that little--

854
01:17:23,940 --> 01:17:25,357
Hello.

855
01:17:31,072 --> 01:17:33,448
Yes! Yes!

856
01:17:33,658 --> 01:17:35,158
The little jerk is armed!

857
01:17:35,368 --> 01:17:39,579
That's it! I'm going in the front.
You go down the basement!

858
01:18:41,934 --> 01:18:44,144
That smart aleck!

859
01:20:12,400 --> 01:20:16,945
Oh, boy. That's it, you little--
You little--

860
01:20:17,905 --> 01:20:20,115
No, not this time, you little brat.

861
01:20:23,452 --> 01:20:26,329
You little creep, where are you?

862
01:20:50,271 --> 01:20:51,688
Yes!

863
01:21:25,431 --> 01:21:27,223
--rip his head off--!

864
01:21:37,109 --> 01:21:38,526
You're dead, kid.

865
01:22:26,033 --> 01:22:28,743
Where are you, you little creep?

866
01:22:44,969 --> 01:22:47,679
Harry, I'm coming in!

867
01:22:52,351 --> 01:22:54,394
Oh, no! I'm really scared.

868
01:22:54,645 --> 01:22:58,440
It's too late for you, kid, we're
in the house. We're gonna get you.

869
01:22:58,691 --> 01:23:00,775
Okay, come and get me!

870
01:23:01,152 --> 01:23:02,277
Why, you--!

871
01:23:08,826 --> 01:23:10,076
Now you're dead!

872
01:23:35,853 --> 01:23:38,354
I'm gonna kill that kid!

873
01:23:53,370 --> 01:23:55,538
-Marv.
-Harry?

874
01:23:55,873 --> 01:23:57,624
Why'd you take your shoes off?

875
01:23:58,167 --> 01:23:59,876
Why are you dressed like a chicken?

876
01:24:01,879 --> 01:24:05,256
I'm up here, you morons.
Come and get me.

877
01:24:08,677 --> 01:24:11,930
You guys give up,
or are you thirsty for more?

878
01:24:21,774 --> 01:24:23,149
Heads up!

879
01:24:26,237 --> 01:24:28,696
Don't worry, Marv.
I'll get him for you.

880
01:24:32,868 --> 01:24:34,536
Yes!

881
01:24:39,083 --> 01:24:41,376
He's only a kid, Harry.
We can take him.

882
01:24:41,544 --> 01:24:44,629
Shut up, will you? What is it?

883
01:24:44,880 --> 01:24:47,006
You're missing some teeth.

884
01:24:47,216 --> 01:24:49,384
Where? It's my gold tooth.

885
01:24:49,593 --> 01:24:52,554
My gold tooth. I'll kill him. I'll kill him!

886
01:24:54,890 --> 01:24:57,100
You bomb me with
one more can, kid...

887
01:24:57,393 --> 01:25:01,563
...and I'll snap off your cojones
and boil them in motor oil!

888
01:25:04,984 --> 01:25:06,109
911 emergency.

889
01:25:06,318 --> 01:25:08,153
Hello, my house is being robbed.

890
01:25:08,404 --> 01:25:13,074
My address is 656 Lincoln Boulevard.
My name is Murphy.

891
01:25:16,579 --> 01:25:17,996
You never know what's there.

892
01:25:19,123 --> 01:25:20,748
There he is!

893
01:25:25,671 --> 01:25:27,338
I got you! I got him, Harry.

894
01:25:29,133 --> 01:25:30,425
I got him.

895
01:25:31,552 --> 01:25:32,844
Harry, give me a hand!

896
01:25:36,223 --> 01:25:38,141
I got him!

897
01:25:38,309 --> 01:25:39,642
Harry, help me. Get up!

898
01:25:41,270 --> 01:25:42,478
I got him.

899
01:26:22,186 --> 01:26:23,478
What are you doing?

900
01:26:24,313 --> 01:26:26,898
Harry, don't move.

901
01:26:27,149 --> 01:26:28,233
Marv?

902
01:26:28,484 --> 01:26:30,818
Don't move.

903
01:26:31,320 --> 01:26:32,862
What are you doing?

904
01:26:37,618 --> 01:26:39,285
Did I get him?

905
01:26:39,745 --> 01:26:41,120
Did I get him?

906
01:26:41,497 --> 01:26:43,581
Where is it? Where is it?

907
01:26:43,791 --> 01:26:47,418
Never mind that. Here!
How do you like it, huh? You jerk!

908
01:26:47,628 --> 01:26:50,505
Get that kid, before I--
Get that kid!

909
01:27:17,157 --> 01:27:18,449
Where'd he go?

910
01:27:19,118 --> 01:27:21,202
Maybe he committed suicide.

911
01:27:21,537 --> 01:27:26,332
Down here, you big horse's ass!
Come get me before I call the police.

912
01:27:26,542 --> 01:27:28,543
-Let's get him!
-Wait, wait.

913
01:27:28,752 --> 01:27:30,628
It's just what he wants us to do:

914
01:27:30,838 --> 01:27:33,923
Go back through his fun house
so we get all tore up.

915
01:27:34,133 --> 01:27:35,675
He's gonna call the cops!

916
01:27:35,884 --> 01:27:37,552
From a tree house?

917
01:27:37,803 --> 01:27:38,928
Come on.

918
01:27:40,180 --> 01:27:41,764
-Out the window?
-Yeah.

919
01:27:41,932 --> 01:27:43,349
I'm not going out the window.

920
01:27:43,559 --> 01:27:47,562
Why, you scared? Are you afraid?
Come on, get out here.

921
01:27:52,401 --> 01:27:53,735
Come on.

922
01:27:59,742 --> 01:28:01,242
Come on!

923
01:28:06,874 --> 01:28:10,126
-Come on. Keep going.
-Let's go back, Harry.

924
01:28:15,758 --> 01:28:16,841
Shut it, Marv.

925
01:28:20,304 --> 01:28:21,346
Hey, guys!

926
01:28:21,930 --> 01:28:23,222
Check this out.

927
01:28:24,308 --> 01:28:26,017
Go back. Go back.

928
01:29:14,525 --> 01:29:15,900
There he is!

929
01:29:16,068 --> 01:29:18,152
Hey, I'm calling the cops!

930
01:29:19,405 --> 01:29:21,906
Wait, wait!
He wants us to follow him.

931
01:29:22,157 --> 01:29:24,075
I got a better idea. Come on.

932
01:29:42,094 --> 01:29:43,302
Hi, pal.

933
01:29:43,720 --> 01:29:46,973
We outsmarted you this time.
Get over here!

934
01:29:53,188 --> 01:29:54,355
What are you gonna do?

935
01:29:54,773 --> 01:29:56,816
I'll do exactly what he did to us.

936
01:29:57,025 --> 01:29:58,860
Burn his head with a blowtorch.

937
01:29:59,069 --> 01:30:01,070
I'll smash his face with an iron.

938
01:30:01,280 --> 01:30:04,115
I'd like to slap him
in the face with a paint can!

939
01:30:04,324 --> 01:30:05,950
Shove a nail through his foot!

940
01:30:06,201 --> 01:30:11,080
I'm gonna bite off every one of
these little fingers, one at a time.

941
01:30:20,382 --> 01:30:22,758
Come on. Let's get you home.

942
01:30:45,741 --> 01:30:48,451
Wow, this is great.

943
01:30:51,788 --> 01:30:54,081
Nice move, leaving the water running.

944
01:30:54,291 --> 01:30:58,127
Now we know each and every house
that you've hit.

945
01:31:01,590 --> 01:31:04,258
We've been looking for you guys
for a long time.

946
01:31:04,510 --> 01:31:07,386
Yeah. Well, remember,
we're the Wet Bandits.

947
01:31:07,763 --> 01:31:11,766
-Wet Bandits, that's W-E-T--
-Shut up! Get in the car!

948
01:31:11,934 --> 01:31:13,559
Hey, come on. Come on.

949
01:31:14,353 --> 01:31:16,854
-Hands off the head, pal!
-Come on.

950
01:32:12,452 --> 01:32:14,370
I'm a bad parent. I'm a bad parent.

951
01:32:14,621 --> 01:32:15,830
No, you're not.

952
01:32:15,998 --> 01:32:18,499
You're beating yourself up there.
This happens.

953
01:32:18,709 --> 01:32:20,418
These things happen.

954
01:32:20,627 --> 01:32:24,505
You want to talk about bad parents?
Look at us.

955
01:32:24,715 --> 01:32:29,468
We're on the road 48, 49 weeks a year.
We hardly see our families.

956
01:32:30,178 --> 01:32:32,430
Joe, over there. Gosh, you know...

957
01:32:32,639 --> 01:32:35,474
...he forgets his kids' names
half the time.

958
01:32:35,684 --> 01:32:38,978
Ziggy over there,
he's never even met his kid.

959
01:32:39,229 --> 01:32:42,982
Eddy.... Let's just hope
none of them write a book about him.

960
01:32:44,109 --> 01:32:47,612
Tell me, have you gone on vacation
and left your child home?

961
01:32:51,033 --> 01:32:52,408
No.

962
01:32:53,201 --> 01:32:56,078
But I did leave one
at a funeral parlor once.

963
01:32:56,913 --> 01:33:00,166
Yeah, it was terrible too.
I was all distraught and everything.

964
01:33:00,375 --> 01:33:04,629
The wife and I, we left the little
tyke there in the funeral parlor.

965
01:33:04,880 --> 01:33:08,549
All day. You know, we went
back at night, when we...

966
01:33:08,759 --> 01:33:11,010
...came to our senses, there he was.

967
01:33:11,261 --> 01:33:14,388
Apparently, he was there
all day with a corpse.

968
01:33:15,432 --> 01:33:18,726
He was okay.
You know, after six, seven weeks.

969
01:33:18,935 --> 01:33:21,395
He came around
and started talking again.

970
01:33:22,773 --> 01:33:25,775
They get over it.
Kids are resilient like that.

971
01:33:25,984 --> 01:33:27,693
We shouldn't talk about this.

972
01:33:27,944 --> 01:33:32,073
-I was just trying to cheer you up.
-I'm sorry I did.

973
01:33:58,350 --> 01:33:59,475
Mom?

974
01:34:04,648 --> 01:34:05,940
Mom?

975
01:34:09,986 --> 01:34:12,029
Mom?

976
01:34:58,368 --> 01:34:59,702
Kevin!

977
01:35:01,246 --> 01:35:02,371
Kevin!

978
01:35:33,737 --> 01:35:35,613
Merry Christmas, sweetheart.

979
01:35:45,040 --> 01:35:47,541
Oh, Kevin, I'm so sorry.

980
01:36:07,479 --> 01:36:09,271
Where's everybody else?

981
01:36:09,981 --> 01:36:11,982
Oh, baby, they couldn't come.

982
01:36:12,192 --> 01:36:13,442
They wanted to so much--

983
01:36:13,652 --> 01:36:18,113
I didn't fall asleep in the back
and drool all over you, did I?

984
01:36:18,323 --> 01:36:20,658
-You do drool!
-Shut up!

985
01:36:23,495 --> 01:36:27,122
Kevin, my boy. How are you?
It's good to see you.

986
01:36:27,332 --> 01:36:29,083
You're all right.

987
01:36:29,584 --> 01:36:30,793
I love you. You okay?

988
01:36:32,462 --> 01:36:33,587
Hey, Kev.

989
01:36:35,924 --> 01:36:38,592
It's cool that you didn't
burn the place down.

990
01:36:40,929 --> 01:36:42,388
Thanks, Buzz.

991
01:36:44,099 --> 01:36:46,100
Wait a minute.
How'd you guys get home?

992
01:36:46,309 --> 01:36:48,811
On the morning flight
you didn't want to wait for.

993
01:36:49,020 --> 01:36:52,273
-Oh, no. Thank you.
-Merry Christmas.

994
01:36:52,482 --> 01:36:53,899
Merry Christmas.

995
01:36:54,526 --> 01:36:56,610
Someone has to find an open store.

996
01:36:56,820 --> 01:36:58,445
I went shopping yesterday.

997
01:37:01,116 --> 01:37:02,658
You, shopping?

998
01:37:02,951 --> 01:37:05,661
I got some milk, eggs
and fabric softener.

999
01:37:07,622 --> 01:37:09,498
-What?
-No kidding?

1000
01:37:09,708 --> 01:37:11,417
What a funny guy.

1001
01:37:11,626 --> 01:37:13,752
What else did you do
while we were away?

1002
01:37:14,921 --> 01:37:17,172
Just hung around.

1003
01:37:19,259 --> 01:37:20,718
Bring your stuff upstairs.

1004
01:37:20,927 --> 01:37:25,472
Shopping? He doesn't know how
to tie his shoe. He's going shopping?

1005
01:37:26,016 --> 01:37:28,684
This is not the Kevin I knew.

1006
01:37:52,292 --> 01:37:53,834
Honey, what's this?

1007
01:38:52,310 --> 01:38:55,729
Kevin! What did you do to my room?

